        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 26 at 4:47PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 447 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Saragosa, or 15 miles south of Toyah, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Saragosa, Toyah Lake, and Verhalen.

This includes Interstate 10 between mile markers 204 and 231.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
